      "side": 1,
      "message": "You\u0027ve got everything right here, but I thought you might like to know why.\n\nThe first address is the offset into the library file (e.g. libvulkan_intel.so) on disk, and the second is the address after it\u0027s been dynamically mapped into the DM process\u0027 memory.  If you were using a debugger, you\u0027d be interested in the second address.\n\nRelative offsets can help refine the line number within a function: abort+0x16a means, in the abort() function,  0x16a\u003d362 bytes in.  We could pin those down further if we wanted to, doing something like this: http://stackoverflow.com/a/23910453",
